1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:02,312
Hey tech enthusiasts, welcome back!

2
00:00:02,312 --> 00:00:11,200
Today we're diving into some seriously cool developments, from a new way to get C performance from Go code to major shifts in online advertising.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:16,587
Plus, we'll look at how AI is getting a memory upgrade and a powerful new partnership.


4
00:00:16,706 --> 00:00:20,106
Imagine writing in Go but getting C-level performance!

5
00:00:20,106 --> 00:00:25,631
That's the promise of Solod, a new subset of Go that translates directly to C code.

6
00:00:25,631 --> 00:00:34,306
This project aims to bring the simplicity of Go to areas traditionally dominated by C, like embedded systems or operating system kernels.

7
00:00:34,306 --> 00:00:41,368
It's a fascinating bridge between two powerful programming paradigms, offering developers the best of both worlds.


8
00:00:41,474 --> 00:00:43,086
A 20-year run has ended!

9
00:00:43,086 --> 00:00:50,661
A prominent blogger, Eric Goldman, has decided to pull the plug on Google AdSense for his websites, effective next year.

10
00:00:50,661 --> 00:00:58,474
After two decades, he's moving on from the platform, citing evolving ad tech and the diminishing returns of traditional display ads.

11
00:00:58,474 --> 00:01:04,799
It's a significant shift for a long-time user, highlighting changes in the digital advertising landscape.


12
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:06,948
Big news in the AI world!

13
00:01:06,948 --> 00:01:12,398
Anthropic is supercharging its future with expanded partnerships with Google and Broadcom.

14
00:01:12,398 --> 00:01:19,860
This collaboration focuses on next-gen compute, meaning more powerful infrastructure for Anthropic's advanced AI models.

15
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:26,310
It's a strategic move to secure the cutting-edge hardware needed to push the boundaries of artificial intelligence.

16
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:30,310
Get ready for even more sophisticated AI innovations!


17
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:32,535
What if AI could remember like a human?

18
00:01:32,535 --> 00:01:38,822
That's the idea behind Hippo, a new biologically inspired memory system for AI agents.

19
00:01:38,822 --> 00:01:46,410
Hippo aims to give AI a more efficient and context-aware way to store and retrieve information, much like our own brains.

20
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:52,772
It's an exciting step towards more sophisticated and intelligent AI systems that can learn and adapt better.


21
00:02:00,874 --> 00:02:02,961
And that's your tech news roundup for today!

22
00:02:02,961 --> 00:02:08,824
From programming breakthroughs to AI advancements and a look into biotech, it's been a packed update.

23
00:02:08,824 --> 00:02:13,711
Don't forget to like, subscribe, and tell us which story caught your attention the most.

24
00:02:13,711 --> 00:02:14,799
See you next time!


